@startuml runtime-sequence-cq-routing-resume-v1
title CQ Routing and Resume (Application Runtime)

participant "Specialist Agent\nAPP-008" as APP_008
participant "PM Agent\nAPP-007" as APP_007
participant "Dashboard Server\nAPP-020" as APP_020
participant "UserInputGateway\nAPP-021" as APP_021
participant "UserInteractionOrchestrator\nAPP-018" as APP_018
participant "LangGraph Orchestrator\nAPP-016" as APP_016
database "EventStore\nAPP-001" as APP_001

APP_008 -> APP_001: record_event(cq.raised)
APP_007 -> APP_001: record_event(cq.batched)
APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(phase.suspended)

APP_020 -> APP_001: query open CQs
APP_020 -> APP_021: delegate CQ answer submission payload
APP_021 -> APP_001: record_event(cq.answered, event_id, cq_id, upload_refs?)
APP_018 -> APP_001: query cq.answered by cq_id
APP_018 -> APP_001: check_dedup(event_id)
alt event_id already processed
	APP_018 -> APP_001: record_event(decision.recorded, decision="duplicate-cq-answer-ignored")
else first-seen event_id
	APP_018 -> APP_001: record_event(cq.routed, correlation_id=cq_id)
	APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(phase.resumed, correlation_id=cq_id)
	APP_016 -> APP_008: resume specialist with CQ answer payload
end

note right of APP_018
Mapped to BPR-003 and cq_user_node
suspend/resume event contract.
Best-practice control points:
- idempotent CQ answer processing via canonical event_id dedup
- correlation_id=cq_id propagation for replay/audit
end note
@enduml
